result.execSummary:
Rodney A Ellena was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Rodney A Ellena was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Case called at 1:16 pm
[Reserve Judge Sarah O'Brien presiding for BrIV]
Defendant Rodney A Ellena in court, in custody, with Attorney Jeffrey DeLaRosa. ADA Monica J Hall appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty De La Rosa submits waiver of extradition form
Court reviews case file documents, Mr. Ellena is being sought by IL, charged with crime of residential burglary
Upon questioning of the Court, Atty De La Rosa confirms that he has advised Mr. Ellena of the penalties of charged crimes
Court reviews letter submitted by Mr. Ellena in which he requests to be transported back to IL ASAP
Court endorses waiver of extradition form, finds that waiver decision has been made freely & voluntarily
Recess: 1:19 pm
mailed to Rodney A Ellena (1) Notice of Hearing - Status Conference on 03-11-2014 at 9:15 am "Return to Sender, Not Deliverable As Addressed, Unable to Forward"
Status conference on March 11, 2014 at 09:15 am.

Case called at 2:02 pm 
Defendant Rodney A Ellena appears in custody, via video, from the Jefferson County Jail with Attorney Jeffrey DeLaRosa. Public Service Special Prosecutor, Melanie Flint appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Service of the Extradition Complaint admitted; Mr. Ellena informs the Court that the dob & address on complaint are correct
Court finds the proceedings are sight and sound sufficient
Atty De La Rosa informs the Court that Def. is eligible for SPD Representation
Atty De La Rosa informs the Court that they have received extradition complaint & supporting documents
Court commits Mr. Ellena to Jefferson County Jail for a period not to exceed 30 days to allow Illinois to obtain Governor's Warrant, but notes that by statute Mr. Ellena is eligible for bond
Bond arguments by Counsel

Court requires a $10000 CASH bond, with no special conditions:

NEXT: (1) STC scheduled for 3/11/14 at 9:15 am - Send notices
